==English==

===Etymology===
Anglo-Norman [[Espayne]], from late Latin [[Spania]], from Latin [[Hispania]], from Greek [[Ἱσπανια]], probably from a Celto-Iberian language (in which ''hi-'' represents the definite article).

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/speɪn/}}
* {{rhymes|eɪn}}

===Proper noun===
'''Spain'''

# Country in [[Europe]]. Member state of the [[European Union]]. Official name: Kingdom of Spain (Reino de España).

